<p id="d1e679">The basic reproduction number, 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="d1e682" display="inline" altimg="si12.svg">
   <mrow>
    <msub>
     <mrow>
      <mi>ℜ</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mn>0</mn>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak" linebreakstyle="after">=</mo>
    <mi>a</mi>
    <mi>β</mi>
    <mo>∕</mo>
    <mi>γ</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>, is equivalent to the more general definition in the text when the rates and probabilities are constant and infectious period is known. The number of new infections at time 
 <italic>t</italic> is 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="d1e706" display="inline" altimg="si13.svg">
   <mrow>
    <mi>λ</mi>
    <mrow>
     <mo>(</mo>
     <mi>t</mi>
     <mo>)</mo>
    </mrow>
    <mi>S</mi>
    <mrow>
     <mo>(</mo>
     <mi>t</mi>
     <mo>)</mo>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> and total number or final size is 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="d1e728" display="inline" altimg="si14.svg">
   <mrow>
    <msubsup>
     <mrow>
      <mo>∫</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mn>0</mn>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mi>∞</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msubsup>
    <mi>λ</mi>
    <mrow>
     <mo>(</mo>
     <mi>t</mi>
     <mo>)</mo>
    </mrow>
    <mi>S</mi>
    <mrow>
     <mo>(</mo>
     <mi>t</mi>
     <mo>)</mo>
    </mrow>
    <mi>d</mi>
    <mi>t</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>. For ease of interpretation, all numbers are plotted as fractions of the total population.
</p>
